reviewText: It's one thing to watch on TV or Hulu/AdultSwim - it's another to OWN. I NEED to hold this in my hands! Please whip the donkeys harder or whatever you do to make DVDs... You guys are part of our lives. We are eating Rolos again and sitting on people's heads. I long for the day when I can crap myself and ask for my D Pants to be hosed off. I begged my wife for some Wait Mates until Iron Man 2 opens. Hot Dogs are on the menu again. Life changing - for the better or worse. You guys are awesome. And it is truly an Awesome Show!

reviewText: sorry tim, sorry eric, but this season felt lacklustre and did not tread any new ground. the standout episode, "snow" is one of the best of all the series (great use of canned laughter) but after that i found myself becoming progressively bored.  let's hope season 5 kicks some ass. great job!

reviewText: Surreality was never this precise, meaningful, and mainstream! Tim & Eric have finally managed to bring surreal humor to the masses! Sure, some Adult Swim viewers don't take kindly to the lack of animation, but that's no reason for cobby-corns to be flyin' pink now, is it?!Surreal humor usually requires an intelligence that many just don't have. You don't "get it"=you call it "a dumb show"! It's as simple as that.
summary: Luis Bunuel is wringing his hands with glee in his grave!
